reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great set for a 2 year old!
reviews.reviewText: My grand daughter just turned 2 and loves this! The pieces are pretty realistic and easy for her to use. It was helpful before her 2 year visit to the doctor last week. She plays with this set several times a day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My Granddaughter loves this!
reviews.reviewText: My 2 year old Granddaughter loves this set. I love how the stethoscope has sounds.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute doctor's kit
reviews.reviewText: Comes with a nice array of doctor's tools. The stethoscope will change from a heart beat to a cough. The cough sounds muffled and took a second to realize that was what was being depicted but that really isn't an issue. The bag is a nice touch as it can be used to hold more toys or items the doctor says are needed. The needle may be a little too long for little one's hands to really use but they eventually grow making this problem really insignificant.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My little grand baby loves the dr kit

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: This was purchased as a "gag" gift for a friend's birthday. It was hilarious and perfect for the situation. It was also very cute and kid friendly. Quite durable, I would say, and the stethoscope made the funniest sounds of a "heartbeat" and a "cough." Very cute. Would make a fun gift for a youngster.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good role playing for future doctors!
reviews.reviewText: Our granddaughter loves playing doctor with these toys. The stethoscope makes a heart beat sound and a coughing sound. The blood pressure cuff can be pumped. The syringe has a movable plunger. We get a whole doctor's exam complete with a bandaid at the end. All the pieces fit in the bag to carry to the next "patient." Very fun and educational for kids.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Dr. kit for toddlers.
reviews.reviewText: This kit comes with several items and all are very cute and sturdy. My granddaughter plays with it all the time and nothing has broken so far. She loves dressing up in the white coat she already had and plays with this kit for hours. Sometimes she is a vet and others a regular Dr. It is well worth the money.
